metadata.name: Sisyphus
metadata.description:
The stone that would never reach the top of the mountain, the same path every day.

Would this be the greatest portrait of the modern worker? if abstraction were understood by everyone, reality would not be seen in the same way.

In this work, I explore the blue tone, which has a content of embracing the envelope, as if a tide completely took over the work, no matter how hard you try, the shapes will not change.
